history.content:
You're taking some heavy-workload techs. I mean 16B shouldn't be too bad for ya since you've taken all the following courses, but it is a lot of homework and lab. If you like data science/the more mathier stuff, you've taken or will be taking all the core (I'm assuming prob 140 will balance out EECS 126). Maybe take it easy because course workloads will be heavy. You could also try expanding into more specialized ML/AI/DS stuff. For example, any applied classes in data science. For me, I'm less into the pure data analysis and like the modeling from it, especially when it comes to signal based things like speech and vision. So courses like 120, 123, 184, and info 159 are useful to me. If you like data analysis for economic contexts, maybe an econ class. Data science is vary broad and you're hitting all the lower divs.

The only other lower div in this area that isn't starting to specialize too much is 182. Idk workload of it though.

I am a junior in EECS and currently planning to take cs 189 and ee 16b next semester, but not sure what to take for my third class. I have already taken cs 188, data 100, prob 140 and all of my breadth + lower division requirements except for physics 7a and 7b. I am really interested in data science as well and wondering what a good (and compatible with the work load) class to add in to my schedule might be. Any suggestions greatly appreciated!
history.subject: Suggestions for course schedule?
